    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your<strong> potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the<strong> chips </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) and drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chips are cooked through and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-halloumi-with-apple-slaw-and-sweet-potato-chips/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Cut your<strong> apple[s]</strong> (skin on) into matchsticks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-halloumi-with-apple-slaw-and-sweet-potato-chips/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>grated carrot </strong>and<strong> apple matchsticks </strong>to a large bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>apple</strong> <strong>slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-halloumi-with-apple-slaw-and-sweet-potato-chips/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>halloumi</strong> into 3 slices per person</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-halloumi-with-apple-slaw-and-sweet-potato-chips/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halloumi slices </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 1-2 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-halloumi-with-apple-slaw-and-sweet-potato-chips/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>and<strong> cider vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>BBQ sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-halloumi-with-apple-slaw-and-sweet-potato-chips/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once golden, add the <strong>BBQ sauce</strong> to the pan with the halloumi and cook for a further 1-2 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>BBQ halloumi</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-halloumi-with-apple-slaw-and-sweet-potato-chips/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> BBQ halloumi</strong> with the<strong> apple slaw</strong> and <strong>chips</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>BBQ sauce </strong>from the pan over the halloumi</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
